<p>An American Daughter is a <ref target="/wiki/Play_(theatre)" title="Play (theatre)">play</ref> written by <ref target="/wiki/Wendy_Wasserstein" title="Wendy Wasserstein">Wendy Wasserstein</ref>. The play takes place in a living room in <ref class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Georgetown,_Washington,_D.C." title="Georgetown, Washington, D.C.">Georgetown, Washington, D.C.</ref></p>

